President Muhammadu Buhari is currently in a closed-door meeting with the governor of Kaduna State Mallam Nasir El-Rufai and the nation’s service chiefs at the presidential villa, Abuja. Inspector General of Police (IGP) Mohammed Adamu, the minister of Defence Masur Dan-Ali, the governor of Adamawa and Borno State are also part of the meeting. Others attending the meeting which is not unconnected with additional security measures for the conduct of the February 23 presidential and March 9 general elections are the Director General of Department of State Services (DSS), Director General of the National Intelligence Agency (NIA) and the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF). <img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Dzw3eLVW0AAwEX8.jpg?resize=740%2C494&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="740" height="494" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-190626" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Dzw3eLVW0AAwEX8.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Dzw3eLVW0AAwEX8.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Dzw3eLVW0AAwEX8.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Dzw3eLVW0AAwEX8.jpg?w=1200&amp;ssl=1 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px" data-recalc-dims="1"> New Telegraph learnt that the meeting is expected to appraise the security challenges of some states perceived to be flashpoints that could hamper the smooth conduct of the forthcoming polls. Details later… <img src="https://i2.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Dzw3fTJX0AAV2h9.jpg?resize=740%2C494&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="740" height="494" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-190627" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Dzw3fTJX0AAV2h9.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.